<task>
Find the methodology files most relevant to what the user is currently working on, based on the session transcript below. Submit them via submit_selection.
</task>

<session_transcript>
{% for entry in messages %}
  <message role="{{ entry.role }}">
{{ entry.text }}
  </message>
{% endfor %}
</session_transcript>

<instruction>
Read the transcript first. Identify the user's task.
{% if two_level_available %}
Then, BEFORE reading any L2 INDEX.xml or leaf files, name explicitly:
  - up to 3 candidate methodology domains from the embedded L1 domains.xml, and
  - up to 2 candidate playbook goal categories from the embedded L1 taxonomy.xml.

State the picks in one short paragraph, then read ONLY those L2 indexes, then submit a selection. Don't Glob the whole tree — let the two-level index route you.
{% else %}
Then search the knowledge tree and submit a selection.
{% endif %}
</instruction>
